com.phonegap.calendar.android.model
Class FeedLink

java.lang.Object
  com.phonegap.calendar.android.model.FeedLink

public class FeedLink
extends java.lang.Object

Represents a logically nested feed. For example, a calendar feed might have a nested feed representing all comments on entries.

Restrictions

  • Either or both of url or #feed must be present.
  • If atom:feed is not present, the client can fetch the contents from the URI in url. If it is present, the contents must the same as what would be retrieved from url at the time the feed was generated.
  • When a PUT or a POST contains a and the url attribute is specified, the attribute's value is used to create a link; if the #feed element is also present, it is ignored. If the url attribute is not specified, then the #feed element is stored as an embedded feed. Note that some services may not support all of these options.

Author:
Nicolas Garnier, Sergio Martinez Rodriguez
